<div id="review_1297000550" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1297000550" />
    <a title="Scott Dow" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/42792240-scott-dow"><img alt="Scott Dow" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1432840594p2/42792240.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1297000550?book_show_action=true">Jun 02, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Scott Dow" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Scott Dow" href="/user/show/42792240-scott-dow">Scott Dow</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1297000550" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer972729312251841076">What a fantastic read, bringing to life the incredibly dangerous and dire circumstances under which early Christianity spread like wild fire. As 21st century Christians in the U.S., we know next to nothing about real faith, sacrifice and persecution. Francine Rivers brings to life a world in which professing belief in Jesus Christ often meant torture, imprisonment or even death. <br/><br/>This trilogy is a compelling read - highly recommended.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


